<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>This interface represents a Wayland surface role given by a Wayland protocol extension that defines how the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtwayland-compositor-waylandsurface.xml">WaylandSurface</db:link> should map onto the screen.</db:para>
<db:para>Note: Even though this type contains a very limited API, the properties and signals of the implementations are named consistently. For example, if you're only using desktop shell extensions in your compositor, it's safe to access properties such as title, maximized, etc. directly on the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtwayland-compositor-shellsurface.xml">ShellSurface</db:link>. See the various implementations for additional properties and signals.</db:para>
